{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"21de5d79-7b1e-4b0d-90b4-39f31e072be1","content":"Here's the scan results for **my_app/**:\n\n### Untestable Static Dependencies Found\n\n| Pattern | File | Line | Call |\n|---------|------|------|------|\n| `datetime.now()` | `views.py` | 3 | `datetime.now()` |\n\n**1 static call site found.**\n\n### Why it's a problem\n`datetime.now()` is called directly, making it impossible to control time in tests — you can't assert exact values or simulate specific dates.\n\n### Recommended fix (Python/Django)\nReplace with Django's `django.utils.timezone.now` and use [`freezegun`](https://github.com/spulec/freezegun) or `unittest.mock.patch` in tests:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()  # timezone-aware + mockable\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nThen in tests:\n```python\nfrom freezegun import freeze_time\n\n@freeze_time(\"2026-01-01\")\ndef test_index(self):\n    ...\n```\n\nNo other untestable statics (file I/O, HTTP, subprocess, env vars) were found. The project is small — just the one `datetime.now()` call to address.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4416479a-8c88-4405-af78-08585c78fadb","outputTokens":311,"requestId":"3405:23F9C7:8DAB7:AEBF6:69F413AB"},"id":"cd384642-d4aa-445e-a604-28aa810d0ea7","timestamp":"2026-05-01T02:45:07.280Z","parentId":"a8a5d520-b114-425c-9d23-d13bf16e965a"}
